
    JS control statements manage the flow of the code execution based on conditions.

    1) Conditional Statements:

        if(condition){

        }

        if(condition){

        }else{

        }

        if(condition){

        }else if(condition2){

        }else if(condition2){

        }else

        switch(condition){
            case 1:
            break;
            case 2:
            break;
            case 3:
            break;
        }

    2) Looping Statements:
        
        i) for loop:

            syntax: 
                for(var count = 0; count < 10; count++){
                    console.log(count);
                }
        
        ii) while loop:
                
                syntax:
                    while(condition is true){

                    }
        
        iii) do while:
                    
        do{

        }while(condition);

    
        iv) for-in:

            var obj = {
                name: "Yash",
                city: "Pune"
            }

            for(var key in obj){
                console.log(key);
            }
        v) for-of:

            var obj = [1,2,3,4];

            for(var val of obj){
                console.log(val);
            }